Task 1
Write a program that prints the ASCII values ​​of characters with indices 65 to 90.
To convert numbers to their corresponding ASCII characters in Java, simply cast the integer to the char type using a cast, e.g., char char = (char) number. Each integer is assigned a character according to the ASCII table.

