Task 6
Write a program that prints all perfect numbers between 1 and 10,000. A perfect number is one whose divisors (excluding itself) sum to that number.
The algorithm for checking whether a number is perfect involves finding the sum of all its divisors less than itself. 
If this sum equals the given number, then the number is perfect. The algorithm works as follows: we iterate through numbers less than the given number, add the divisors, and finally compare the sum to the given number.

